## Additional Information

### Educational Use Notice

AI-STER is designed specifically for educational purposes, including but not
limited to student teacher evaluations, educational assessment, and academic
research. While this software is provided under the MIT License allowing 
commercial use, we encourage institutions and organizations to consider the
educational mission and community benefit when using this software.

### Utah State Board of Education (USBE) Compliance

This software implements evaluation rubrics and standards based on Utah State
Board of Education requirements (July 2024). While every effort has been made
to ensure compliance, users are responsible for verifying that their use of
this software meets current regulatory requirements and institutional policies.

### AI and Data Privacy

This software may integrate with third-party AI services (such as OpenAI).
Users are responsible for:
- Ensuring compliance with data privacy regulations (FERPA, etc.)
- Managing API keys and access credentials securely
- Understanding the data handling practices of integrated AI services
- Obtaining necessary permissions for AI-assisted evaluation content

